        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A lump of bluish ooze shot through with what look like tiny silver shavings of metal. Once it has been activated, it glows with arcs of electricity that leap out at nearby targets.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>Two successful @Check[arcana|dc:21] or @Check[occultism|dc:21] (trained) checks on the oozeshardling to disperse its power, or @Check[acrobatics|dc:23] or @Check[thievery|dc:23] (expert) to remove the flecks of empowering warshard from within the oozeshardling. A failed Acrobatics or Thievery check to disable an oozeshardling results in the creature attempting the check taking @Damage[1d6[acid]] damage (@Damage[2d6[acid]] on a critical failure).</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 6
            },
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Society Scenario #6-07: A God Falls Where Magic Fails"
            },
            "reset": "<p>The oozeshardling node collapses and melds back into the oozeshard after 1 minute, or disappears entirely if the oozeshard is slain.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(3 actions) The oozeshardling uses its first action to make an electric spark Strike against one random non-ooze creature within range, its second action is used to move straight in a random cardinal direction (roll [[/gmr 1d4 #Direction]] to determine the direction), and its third action to make a second electric spark Strike against a different random non-ooze creature within range. The oozeshardling doesn't take a multiple attack penalty.</p>"
